{ I didn't see the need to try and be more clever than transposing to my Najdorf course recommendation. However, against the  6.Nge2  plan I propose a harmonious e6/Nge7 setup, when previously I recommended Nf6, transposing to another tricky position, which we don't have to deal with here, as we start with the 2...g6 move order and not 2...d6. From now on, besides  6.Nge2  , all the variations are taken from my recent Najdorf course. }
